The paper focuses on applying the MAP-Elites algorithm to constrained optimization problems, which is a subfield of optimization and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves evaluating the algorithm's performance on various benchmark problems, which falls under the category of experimental evaluation and analysis, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of visualization techniques, which is a subfield of data visualization and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. The paper also involves optimization and control, which falls under the category of systems and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves optimization and algorithms, which falls under the category of optimization and operations research, making cs.OH (Optimization and Control) a possible category.
